CompileScript: echo "nothing to do"
InstallScript: <<
mkdir -p %i
mv texmf.cnf %i
mkdir -p %i/share/doc/tetex-texmf
mv tetex-LICENSE %i/share/doc/tetex-texmf/LICENSE
mv tetex-ChangeLog %i/share/doc/tetex-texmf/ChangeLog
mkdir -p %i/share/texmf
chmod 755 %i/share/texmf
mkdir -p %i/etc/ls-R
mv ls-R %i/etc/ls-R/texmf
ln -s %p/etc/ls-R/texmf %i/share/texmf/ls-R
mv * %i/share/texmf

echo "files in tetex-base package"
rm %i/share/texmf/dvips/gsftopk/render.ps
rm %i/share/texmf/dvips/base/*.pro
rm %i/share/texmf/fontname/*.map
rm %i/share/texmf/web2c/*.pool
rm %i/share/texmf/web2c/*.tcx
rm %i/share/texmf/web2c/fmtutil.cnf
rm %i/share/texmf/web2c/mktex.opt
rm %i/share/texmf/web2c/mktexdir*
rm %i/share/texmf/web2c/mktexnam*
rm %i/share/texmf/web2c/mktexupd
rm %i/share/texmf/web2c/texmf.cnf

echo "files in context package"
rm -R %i/share/texmf/context
rm %i/share/texmf/doc/context/base/context.rme
rm %i/share/texmf/doc/context/base/minstall.pdf
rm %i/share/texmf/doc/context/base/mreadme.pdf
rm %i/share/texmf/dvips/config/context.map
rm -R %i/share/texmf/fonts/tfm/hoekwater
rm -R %i/share/texmf/fonts/type1/hoekwater/context
rm -R %i/share/texmf/metapost/context
rm -R %i/share/texmf/tex/context
rm -R %i/share/texmf/tex/generic/context

echo "files in hyperref package"
rm -R %i/share/texmf/tex/latex/hyperref
<<
License: Restrictive
Description: Main texmf tree for a teTeX installation
DescPort: <<
The files pdftex.def and texinfo.tex are updated by a patch.
An edited version of Gerben Wierda's texmf.cnf.macosx file is brought in
 via a patch.  (The edit adds four lines for xdvi support).  The file is 
 then edited to replace SELFAUTOPARENT with SELFAUTODIR (since we are not
 putting our binaries in a subdirectory) and to give the correct location 
 of the README file.  Note that the README file in question is actually 
 supplied by the tetex-macosx package, and that xdvi is also a separate 
 package.
<<
DescPackaging: >>
Updated versions of the removed files are supplied by the tetex-base,
 context, and hyperref packages. 
We store the ls-R files of the texmf trees in %p/etc/ls-R/ because they will 
 change after installation.  Other packages should use %p/bin/mktexlsr 
 (not texhash) to update these, and they should take care to update in
 a PostRmScript as well if they have modified these files during or after 
 installation.
<<
